    <summary>Post-detection DFIR analysis layer: correlate your tools' verdicts into one timeline, findings, attacker path, and report — all on localhost.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## DFIR Companion

A **localhost** DFIR analysis tool. It is a *post-detection analysis layer*, **not** a
detection engine — it ingests the verdicts/hits your existing tools already produce
(Velociraptor, Security Onion, Chainsaw, Hayabusa, THOR, EDR/SIEM, KAPE, Volatility,
CloudTrail, M365, email, sandbox reports, …), correlates them across tools into **one
forensic timeline**, and synthesizes findings, MITRE ATT&CK mapping, the attacker path,
and a court-ready report — the "so what" layer.

This package installs the **portable Windows build** (a Node single-executable; no Node.js
install required). After install, run it from any console:

```
dfir-companion
```

then open **http://127.0.0.1:4773/dashboard**.

### Where your data lives

The companion binds **127.0.0.1 only** (never your network). On a Chocolatey install:

* **Config** → `%LOCALAPPDATA%\DFIR-Companion\.env` (seeded from the bundled example; the
  installer points the server at it via the `DFIR_ENV_FILE` environment variable). Edit it to
  configure the AI provider/model/key and threat-intel keys (all optional — capture and the
  deterministic importers work with AI off).
* **Cases + state** → `%LOCALAPPDATA%\DFIR-Companion\cases` (written as `DFIR_CASES_ROOT` in
  that `.env`, so evidence is never written to the admin-owned install dir).

### Upgrade / uninstall

* `choco upgrade dfir-companion` pulls the next release.
* `choco uninstall dfir-companion` removes the binary, shim, and the environment variables.
  **Your cases and config are left in place** at `%LOCALAPPDATA%\DFIR-Companion` — delete
  that folder by hand if you no longer need the evidence.

### Notes

* No inbound firewall rule is created or needed — the server is localhost-only by design.
* The companion does **not** send anything externally unless you opt in to threat-intel
  enrichment per case.
]]></description>
